In this statement, the President acknowledges Holocaust Remembrance Day and emphasizes the importance of honoring the victims and ensuring their memory remains alive. He recalls his visits to Buchenwald and Yad Vashem, where he witnessed the horrors of anti-Semitism and the Nazis' campaign to annihilate the Jewish people. Despite the atrocities, he highlights the dignity and courage displayed by those who endured the Holocaust, reminding us of humanity's capacity for decency and compassion. The President calls for the prevention of genocide, the confrontation of anti-Semitism and prejudice, and the rejection of hateful stereotypes against the Jewish people. He emphasizes the need to work towards a world of justice and peace, where all nations and people value the shared humanity and inherent dignity of every individual.